    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically someone else just keeps the money safe so nobody gets ripped off. who usually acts as this third party? like is it my lawyer or something else?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly, it's like a safety net to prevent any mischief. The third party in an escrow arrangement is usually an escrow company or an attorney, not your lawyer. An escrow company is a specialized business that deals with holding funds and documents until the conditions of a transaction are met. However, an attorney can also act as an escrow agent, especially in real estate transactions in some regions. They ensure that the funds are released only when all the agreed-upon conditions are fulfilled, such as the closing of the sale and the transfer of the property deed. In your house-buying scenario, it's likely that an escrow company will handle the transaction, but it's always good to confirm with your realtor or the closing agent.",
